{{Infobox Radio station | name = WXTG | image = [[Image:WXTG-AMFM 2009.PNG]] | city = [[Hampton, Virginia]] | area = [[Virginia Peninsula|Peninsula]] of [[Hampton Roads]] | branding = ''"The Game 102.1"'' | slogan = | airdate = [[1948 in radio|1948]] | frequency = 1490 [[Kilohertz|kHz]] | format = [[Sports radio|Sports Radio]] | power = 970 [[Watt]]s day and night | class = C | facility_id = 25917 | coordinates = {{coord|37|1|50.0|N|76|22|32.0|W|type:landmark}} | callsign_meaning = '''WX''' '''T'''he '''G'''ame | former_callsigns = | affiliations = [[Fox Sports Radio]] | owner = [[Red Zebra Broadcasting]] | licensee = Red Zebra Broadcasting Licensee (Norfolk), LLC | sister_stations = [[WXTG-FM]] | webcast = [http://lightningstream.surfernetwork.com/Media/player/view/wxtg_sl2.asp?StreamingServerName=nick11a&call=wxtg WXTG Webstream] | website = [http://www.1021thegame.com/ WXTG Online] }} '''WXTG''' is a [[Sports radio|Sports Radio]] formatted [[Broadcasting|broadcast]] [[radio station]] licensed to [[Hampton, Virginia]], serving the [[Virginia Peninsula|Peninsula]] of [[Hampton Roads]]. WXTG is owned and operated by [[Red Zebra Broadcasting]].
Prior to 2007, WXTG was known as '''WLRT''' and carried a hybrid [[talk radio]]/[[country music]] format.[http://web.archive.org/web/20070318001537/http://www.1490theoutlaw.com/schedule.asp]
